727
A IMPORTANT INFORMATION
FOR OUR 727 FANJET PASSENGERS
Even though you may be an experi-
enced air traveler, there are certain
features of this, the most modern of
air transports, with which you may
not be familiar.
PACIFIC SOUTHWEST AIRLINES
AUTOMATIC OXYGEN SYSTEM
The higher altitudes at which this aircraft operates require the
prompt use of the automatic oxygen system in case of any
sudden change in cabin pressure. Should a decompression occur
oxygen masks will drop down. Take nearest mask and promptly
place over nose and mouth. Adjust Headband. Breathe normally.
